," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk.<\/strong> Add egg yolk, eggs and reserved milled sugar and mix <b>4 min\/speed 4<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add vanilla and brewed espresso and mix <b>15 sec\/speed 3<b>. Add reserved whipped cream and combine <b>10 sec\/\/speed 2<b>. Pour chocolate mixture over frozen base and spread over evenly using spatula. Cover with plastic wrap and place into freezer for a minimum of 6 hours or overnight. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Champagne snaps","content":["Preheat oven to 220°C. Grease a baking tray (30 x 40 cm). Line with a large piece of baking paper to completely cover base and sides of tray (to ensure all toffee stays on the baking paper).","Spread almonds onto baking tray and bake for 3 minutes (220°C) or until lightly golden. Transfer almonds into a bowl and set aside.","Place sugar into mixing bowl and mill <b>10 sec\/speed 9<b>.","Add Champagne and cook <b>13 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>, placing simmering basket instead of measuring cup onto mixing bowl lid. Carefully pour mixture onto lined baking tray. Bake for 4 minutes (220°C), then remove from oven and carefully tilt tray from side-to-side to evenly distribute mixture around the tray. Place back into oven and bake for 1 minute (220°C). Remove from oven and carefully tilt tray from side-to-side to evenly distribute mixture. Place back into oven and bake for a further 1 minute (220°C). Remove from oven and carefully tilt tray from side-to-side to evenly distribute mixture. Toffee should now be a dark amber colour. Sprinkle toffee with reserved almonds and allow to cool completely (approx. 30 minutes).","Remove cake from tin and transfer onto a serving plate. Break Champagne toffee into pieces and decorate cake just before serving."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Coffee almond base","content":["80 g raw sugar","400 g pouring (whipping) cream","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","1 egg white","1 tbsp instant granulated coffee","1 pinch salt","60 g slivered almonds, lightly toasted"]},{"title":"Coffee chocolate top","content":["100 g raw sugar","300 g pouring (whipping) cream","200 g dark chocolate (70% cocoa), broken into pieces","1 egg yolk","2 eggs","1 tsp natural vanilla extract","2 tbsp espresso coffee, brewed"]},{"title":"Champagne snaps","content":["butter, for greasing","40 g flaked almonds","130 g raw sugar","100 g Champagne (see Tips)"]}],"id":"r108764","imageLink":"https:\/\/3.bp.blogspot.com\/-lI2-6DBfH2U\/XZWcoemLuFI\/AAAAAAAAecc\/PRfnfnPNK2Ai7Te0Xg2Y3z-bCcnUEnMQgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_2v_n8A0FQRrV8YiH.png","title":"Mocha ice cream cake with Champagne snaps","publishedAt":"2016-04-17T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"6 g","fat":"32.4 g","uom":"per 1 slice","carbohydrates":"38.8 g","calories":"1933 kJ \/ 460 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking paper, springform cake tin (20 cm), bowl, plastic wrap, serving plate, baking tray (30 x 40 cm), freezer, oven","hintsAndTricks":["You can replace the Champagne with sparkling wine.","To save time, make the ice cream cake in advance and store in the freezer."],"basicInfo":["medium","35m","9h 40m","12 slices"]}